                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/327</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]<note n="1" xml:id="d269fn1">Printed
                            in full in <ref target="frus1918Russiav01#pg_27">vol. <hi
                                    rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 27</ref>.</note>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-21T15:00:00+02:31">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 21, 1917, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received April 23, 9.30 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1211. … Very important, however, that congestion at Vladivostok and on Siberian
                    Railway be relieved by prompt shipment of railroad equipment and arrival of
                    strong experienced manager. Situation offers excellent opportunity which our
                    ablest managers should be ambitious to embrace. British Ambassador tells me
                    unofficially that he recommends Russian Government to give us control at
                    Vladivostok and of entire Siberian Railway. English have control at
                    Archangel.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
